7. Bayesian Optimal Experimental Design for Parameter Estimation

7.1 Bayesian Inference Framework

Kinetic and deactivation parameters are treated as random variables \boldsymbol{\theta} with prior distribution p(\boldsymbol{\theta}). Given experimental data \mathcal{D}, Bayes' theorem yields the posterior distribution:

p(\boldsymbol{\theta} \mid \mathcal{D}) = \frac{p(\mathcal{D} \mid \boldsymbol{\theta}) \, p(\boldsymbol{\theta})}{p(\mathcal{D})}.

The likelihood p(\mathcal{D} \mid \boldsymbol{\theta}) incorporates both measurement error and model discrepancy.

7.2 Expected Information Gain and BOED

The utility of a candidate experiment with design \xi is the expected reduction in entropy of the posterior:

U(\xi) = \mathbb{E}_{y \sim p(y \mid \xi)}\left[ D_{\mathrm{KL}}\left( p(\boldsymbol{\theta} \mid y, \xi) \,\|\, p(\boldsymbol{\theta}) \right) \right],

where D_{\mathrm{KL}} is the Kullback-Leibler divergence. BOED selects the design \xi^* that maximizes U(\xi).

7.3 Multi-Objective Bayesian Optimization

For simultaneous optimization of methane yield and deactivation rate, we employ the Expected Hypervolume Improvement (EHVI) acquisition function:

\alpha_{\mathrm{EHVI}}(\xi) = \mathbb{E}\left[ \max(0, \mathrm{HV}(\mathcal{P} \cup \{f(\xi)\}) - \mathrm{HV}(\mathcal{P})) \right],

where \mathcal{P} is the current Pareto front and \mathrm{HV} is the hypervolume indicator. BOED has been shown to reduce the number of experiments required for convergence from hundreds to tens.

7.4 Parameter Identifiability and the Chlorine-Coking Interaction

Due to strong correlation between chlorine poisoning and coking rate, the uncertainty in the interaction term \theta_{\mathrm{Cl}} \times C_{\mathrm{coke}} is expected to remain high even after accelerated aging. The BOED acquisition function is augmented with a penalty on expected posterior variance to prioritize experiments that decorrelate these parameters. The final GP surrogate reports widened confidence intervals for predictions involving high Cl and high coke simultaneously.

