13. Discussion: Critical Advice Integration and Synthesis

This chapter synthesizes the critical advice received during the development of this thesis and documents how each observation has been integrated into the final framework.

13.1 Correction of the Lyapunov Stability Proof

Issue Identified: The original formulation L(s) = -V(s) with \dot{L}(s) \leq 0 implied \dot{V}(s) \geq 0, contradicting stability.

Resolution: The framework was revised to employ separate Control Lyapunov Function (CLF) and Control Barrier Function (CBF) constraints. The CLF condition \dot{V} \leq -\alpha V guarantees exponential convergence, while the CBF condition \dot{h} + \gamma h \geq 0 guarantees forward invariance of the safe set. This clean separation provides formal guarantees of both stability and safety.

13.2 Correction of the Regeneration ODE

Issue Identified: The term \partial a_{\text{recover}}/\partial t = k_{\text{reg}} C_{\text{coke}} a implies recovery rate increases with coke, creating non-physical feedback.

Resolution: The regeneration term was reformulated as k_{\text{reg}}(T) P_{\text{H}_2} (1 - a) \theta_{\text{coke,reversible}}, driven by hydrogen partial pressure and the fraction of reversible coke. This ensures recovery asymptotically approaches full activity as coke is removed.

13.3 Correction of Equilibrium Constant Calculation

Issue Identified: Arithmetic slip in K_p(573) calculation and unit ambiguity.

Resolution: The calculation was corrected to K_p(573) \approx 6.23, and the reference pressure P^\circ = 1\ \mathrm{bar} was explicitly stated to ensure dimensionless equilibrium constant.

13.4 Reclassification of PINN Error Bound

Issue Identified: The claimed "theorem" assumed Lipschitz continuity of the DGM operator without proof.

Resolution: The bound was relabeled as a "heuristic error estimate" and presented as a practical diagnostic rather than a formal theorem.

13.5 Replacement of Catalyst Health "Theorem"

Issue Identified: Claim of monotonicity in \mathcal{H} is impossible due to inherent sintering.

Resolution: The false theorem was replaced with a "Bounded Degradation Rate" proposition, acknowledging that health degrades over time but the controller minimizes the degradation rate.

