14. Conclusion and Outlook

This thesis has presented a comprehensive, mathematically rigorous framework for the design, modeling, and autonomous control of a Mars ISRU Sabatier reactor capable of reliable, long-duration methane production. The key contributions are:

1. A validated multi-physics model that couples Dusty Gas Model transport, extended LHHW kinetics with contaminant inhibition, and spatially resolved deactivation dynamics, benchmarked against the latest experimental literature.
2. A novel catalyst health mapping framework that quantifies the cumulative effects of coking, sintering, and chlorine poisoning, enabling real-time state estimation and predictive maintenance.
3. A Lyapunov-constrained safe reinforcement learning controller that provides formal guarantees of closed-loop stability and safety while autonomously managing reactor operation across power cycles and fault scenarios.

The proposed five-phase research plan culminates in a 500-hour integrated demonstration at TRL 5–6, targeting >99% methane conversion, >98% selectivity, and >80% catalyst activity retention with fully autonomous operation.

The open-source deliverables—including kinetic libraries, the PINN-GP surrogate, and the validated RL policy—will serve as foundational resources for the global Mars ISRU community. This work directly addresses NASA's stated priorities on scaling reactor size, proper start-up and shutdown sequences, and catalyst health and lifetime, establishing a definitive pathway toward reliable, autonomous propellant production on Mars.

Future work should extend this framework to:

· Co-electrolysis integration for direct CO₂/H₂O co-conversion.
· Sabatier-RWGS dual-reactor architectures for enhanced CO₂ utilization.
· Full system-level optimization including electrolyzer and cryocooler dynamics.

The successful deployment of this technology will make sustained human presence on Mars architecturally and economically viable, transforming the Red Planet from a destination of flags and footprints into a new home for humanity.

